<!-- HOW IT WORKS — 4 STEPS -->
<section class="section-white">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label">How it works</div>
    <h2>From the first ring to<br/>a resolved incident.</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">Tenants don't download apps. They don't log into portals. They call the number — the same way they'd call any business — and Aitha PM takes it from there.</p>
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-num-wrap"><div class="step-num">1</div><div class="step-line"></div></div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <div class="step-title">Tenant calls in</div>
          <div class="step-desc">The tenant calls your property's dedicated phone number. Aitha PM answers, lets them know they've reached the property management line, and asks them to describe what they need. No menus, no hold music. Just leave a message.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-num-wrap"><div class="step-num">2</div><div class="step-line"></div></div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <div class="step-title">Voicemail transcribed instantly</div>
          <div class="step-desc">The moment the tenant hangs up, Aitha PM transcribes the voicemail. Within seconds the message exists as text the AI can read, reason about, and act on. Whether they called from a cell phone or a landline — the system handles both.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-num-wrap"><div class="step-num">3</div><div class="step-line"></div></div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <div class="step-title">AI classifies the issue</div>
          <div class="step-desc">Aitha PM reads the transcription and classifies it in under five seconds — safety emergency, information request, self-fixable maintenance, or vendor-needed maintenance. Each path leads to a different response, immediate and appropriate to the urgency level.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-num-wrap"><div class="step-num">4</div><div class="step-line"></div></div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <div class="step-title">The right response goes out</div>
          <div class="step-desc">The tenant gets a reply — by text if they called from a cell, by callback if they called from a landline. The on-call contact gets notified when and only when human involvement is actually needed. Everything is logged to the dashboard the moment it happens.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FOUR PATHS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label">Four paths</div>
    <h2>Every call goes somewhere.<br/>Nothing falls through.</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">The classification determines what happens next. No two calls are treated the same — because no two calls are the same.</p>
    <div class="paths">
      <div class="path-card red">
        <div class="path-icon">🚨</div>
        <div class="path-title">Safety emergency</div>
        <div class="path-desc">Gas smell, flooding, fire, electrical hazard. Bypasses every queue. The tenant gets emergency instructions immediately. The on-call contact gets a call and a text at the same time. No delay, no approval needed.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="path-card blue">
        <div class="path-icon">📄</div>
        <div class="path-title">Information request</div>
        <div class="path-desc">Lease questions, rent due dates, vacancy inquiries, payment links, move-out procedures, policy questions. AI answers directly from the property's knowledge base. Tenant gets their answer in under a minute without the manager picking up the phone.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="path-card green">
        <div class="path-icon">🔧</div>
        <div class="path-title">Self-fixable maintenance</div>
        <div class="path-desc">Tripped breaker, clogged drain, running toilet, GFCI reset, AC filter, pilot light. AI walks the tenant through it step by step. If it doesn't work — or they decline — the call moves to vendor dispatch automatically.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="path-card">
        <div class="path-icon">🏗️</div>
        <div class="path-title">Vendor dispatch</div>
        <div class="path-desc">HVAC failure, major plumbing, electrical, structural. AI identifies the trade, texts the on-call contact a numbered vendor list, dispatches whoever they select, sends the work order, confirms acceptance, and updates the tenant — all without a single phone call from the manager.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

