<section class="section-navy">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label teal">Who it's for</div>
    <h2 class="light">Built for every size.<br/>Residential and commercial.</h2>
    <p class="section-intro light">The same system works differently depending on who's running it — from a solo landlord to a portfolio management company.</p>
    <div class="operator-grid">
      <div class="op-card">
        <div class="op-tag">Small residential</div>
        <div class="op-title">1–10 properties · Owner-managed</div>
        <div class="op-desc">The owner is the manager, the maintenance coordinator, and the after-hours contact. Every tenant call goes to their personal cell.</div>
        <div class="op-wins">
          <div class="op-win">Personal cell stays private — tenants call the property number</div>
          <div class="op-win">Information requests and self-fixes resolved without you</div>
          <div class="op-win">Weekend calls arrive as structured texts, not voicemail piles</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="op-card">
        <div class="op-tag">Mid-size residential</div>
        <div class="op-title">10–100 units · Small team</div>
        <div class="op-desc">A manager, possibly an assistant, and a maintenance tech covering multiple properties. The tech is stretched thin. After-hours calls end up on everyone's phone.</div>
        <div class="op-wins">
          <div class="op-win">Each property gets its own number and escalation chain</div>
          <div class="op-win">Tech only gets called when a vendor is actually needed</div>
          <div class="op-win">Self-fixes reduce unnecessary dispatch by 30–40%</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="op-card">
        <div class="op-tag">Large residential</div>
        <div class="op-title">100+ units · HUD · RD · LIHTC</div>
